This demo presents BlueTag, a permanently deployed underwater sensor system based on backscatter communication. BlueTag is a battery-powered CTD (conductivity, temperature, depth) sensor that transmits measurements every 15 minutes to a remote base station via underwater backscatter. The base station archives these measurements and publishes them online. Unlike prior underwater backscatter systems limited to short-term laboratory experiments, BlueTag has been deployed in the Charles River in Boston, MA since July 9th, 2025, marking the first long-term underwater backscatter deployment of its kind to sense meaningful environmental data. Live data from this deployment is available publicly at https://sk-exp-server.mit.edu/.